+---------------------------------------------------+
| How to run examples under GXTracking/mic/tbb/test |
+---------------------------------------------------+

1. Assume that the Intel(R) MIC device (Xeon Phi) is available and a cross
   compiler is installed at /usr/linux-k1om-4.7
   
   Otherwise, modify the following line in CMakeLists.txt 
   with an alternative cuda path on your system;

   SET(MIC_TOOLKIT_ROOT_DIR "/usr/linux-k1om-4.7")

2. How to build an example from  GXTracking/mic/omp directory

   . setenv.sh   
   mkdir bin 
   cd bin
   cmake -DProject=stepper -DUSE_MIC=ON ..
   make

3. How to run

   3.1 link data (EM tables, Magnetic field map, brem_SB)

   ln -s ../../../data  data   

   3.2 run the test engine

   ./stepper <run_option>

   where <run option>: 1 - ClassicalRK4
                       2 - CashKarpRKF45
                       3 - NystromRK4
